        <abstract>
            <p>Spiralling of tendrils.</p> 
<p>Has worked hard on <hi rend="italic">Drosera</hi>.</p>  
<p>Is interested in tracing the "nerves" of <hi rend="italic">Dionaea</hi> which follow the vascular bundles. Finds he can paralyse half of the leaf by pricking it at a certain point.</p>  
<p>Wishes AG to carry out two experiments on <hi rend="italic">D. filiformis</hi>.</p>  
<p>Has received AG’s Dubuque address [<hi rend="italic">Am. J. Sci.</hi> 3d ser. 4 (1872): 282–98].</p> 
        </abstract>
